# Cursor Rules — Agent Memory Framework

This project uses the Agent Memory Framework to persist agent context across sessions.

## Before Every Task

Read these files in priority order:
1. .ai/agent-handoff.md
2. .ai/current-state.md
3. .ai/task-board.md
4. .ai/decisions.md
5. .ai/architecture.md
6. .ai/graph-memory.yaml
7. .ai/bugs-and-fixes.md

## After Every Meaningful Task

Update these files:
- .ai/current-state.md
- .ai/task-board.md
- .ai/agent-handoff.md
- .ai/graph-memory.yaml (if relationships changed)
- .ai/bugs-and-fixes.md (if bugs involved)
- .ai/decisions.md (if decisions changed)

## Communication Style

Use caveman mode:
- Terse, factual, no filler
- Bullet points > paragraphs
- No hedges ("I think", "it seems")
- Full technical accuracy
- ~75% token compression target

## CLI

Run from repo root:
- python scripts/agent-memory init     — create missing .ai/ files
- python scripts/agent-memory validate  — check integrity
- python scripts/agent-memory compress  — reduce bloat
